<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870126-0125 </DOCNO><HL> Dividend News:South Jersey Industries Inc.</HL><DD> 01/26/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SJIDIVIDENDS (DIV) </IN><TEXT>   SOUTH JERSEY INDUSTRIES INC. said it plans to propose to shareholders, at its annual meeting April 23, a 2-for-1 stock split and an increase in authorized shares to 20 million from 7.5 million. Under the proposal, the natural gas distributor and minerals concern would have 7.6 million shares outstanding. Currently, it has 3.8 million shares outstanding. The record and payable dates for the split haven't been determined. The Folsom, N.J., company said it believes that increasing authorized shares will allow more flexibility for possible acquisitions and future financings. </TEXT></DOC>